<section class="section section--tight">
  <div class="container faq-grid">
    <details class="faq-item card reveal" data-reveal open>
      <summary>What is a Loan Estimate (LE)?</summary>
      <p class="muted">A standardized disclosure that outlines key terms, projected payments, and closing costs. It helps you compare offers on an apples-to-apples basis within the regulatory timing window.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item card reveal" data-reveal style="--delay: 40ms">
      <summary>Rate vs. APR — why both appear</summary>
      <p class="muted">The interest rate is the cost of borrowing the principal. The APR includes certain fees and prepaid finance charges expressed as an annual percentage, which can make it easier to compare total cost across lenders.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item card reveal" data-reveal style="--delay: 80ms">
      <summary>Debt-to-income (DTI) in plain terms</summary>
      <p class="muted">Lenders compare your monthly obligations (housing, debts, some installment items) to your qualifying monthly income. We review DTI early so you understand how a car payment or student loan affects purchasing power.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item card reveal" data-reveal style="--delay: 120ms">
      <summary>Pre-approval vs. pre-qualification</summary>
      <p class="muted">Pre-qualification is often a lighter review. Pre-approval typically involves documented income and assets so sellers and listing agents take your offer more seriously.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item card reveal" data-reveal style="--delay: 160ms">
      <summary>What happens at closing?</summary>
      <p class="muted">You sign final loan and title documents, funds are disbursed per the settlement statement, and ownership transfers (purchase) or your new loan replaces the old one (refinance). We walk you through the Closing Disclosure beforehand.</p>
    </details>
  </div>
</section>

